 Commemorating the life and times of Australia's 22nd prime minister,       
 Malcolm Fraser, SBS pays tribute with this documentary that explores the   
 evolution of the man and the truth behind the public myth.                 
                                                                            
 Malcolm Fraser served as Australia's prime minster from November 11, 1975  
 to March 11, 1983 and was an integral, and often controversial, part of    
 Australia's political history.                                             
                                                                            
 Tracing his political career, this documentary explores the perception of  
 Fraser as a conservative and ruthless politician; an 'enemy of the         
 people', for bringing down the first Labor government in 23 years. Years   
 later, public perception of Malcolm Fraser has changed - with people who   
 were against him now embracing his humility, his 'radical' stance on       
 reconciliation, asylum seekers and globalisation. Fraser has become a 'man 
 of the people' and a champion of the disenfranchised.
